Definition: an organelle in the cytoplasm of a living cell
Example: they attach to mRNA and move down it one codon at a time and then stop until tRNA brings the required amino acid; when it reaches a stop codon it falls apart and releases the completed protein molecule for use by the cell; the ribosome is the site of protein synthesis
Synonyms: organelle, an, in, the, cytoplasm, of, a, living, cell, they, attach, to, mRNA, and, move, down, it, one, codon, at, time, then, stop, until, tRNA, brings, required, amino, acid, when, reaches, falls, apart, releases, completed, protein, molecule, for, use, by, is, site, synthesis
Category: noun.body
